cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the impact of relay selection on the performance of cooperative NOMA networks, which involves analyzing the information transmission and processing aspects of the system. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with relay selection in cooperative networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of different relay selection schemes in cooperative NOMA networks, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with cooperative communication and relay selection, which are core topics in communication and networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may have implications for multimedia applications that rely on cooperative communication and relay selection for efficient data transmission.
